<div id="main-content">
    
<div class="container" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="span2">
            <section class="article-brief">
                 <h2>About Find a Solicitor <i class="sprite icon-the-law-society pull-right"></i></h2>
<p>Run by the Law Society, Find a Solicitor is a free service for anyone looking for information about organisations or people providing legal services in England and Wales that are regulated by the Solicitors Regulation Authority (SRA). Find a Solicitor takes data held by the SRA, which we adapt and add additional information to, and present through an easy-to-use search. While we try to ensure the accuracy of the information, the Law Society cannot accept any liability arising from your reliance upon it, or from the inclusion in it or omission from it of any data whatsoever.<p>
            </section>
            <section class="article-brief">
                <h2>Law Society member support <i class="sprite icon-cell-phone pull-right"></i></h2>
<p>If you need help amending information about you on Find a Solicitor or wish to give other feedback about the website, please call +44 (0)20 7320 5757 (Monday to Friday from 09:00 to 17:00 <span class="bold">charged at local call rates</span>) or <a href="mailto:thesupportcentre@lawsociety.org.uk?subject=FAS%20Member%20enquiry">email us</a>.</p>
            </section>       
        </div>

        <div class="span2">
            <section class="article-brief">
                <h2>Getting help with your legal issue  <i class="sprite icon-jury-hammer pull-right"></i></h2>
<p>Use 'quick search' to find your nearest legal practice. Simply choose a legal issue and add your location. Use 'pro search' to find a specific organisation or person by name or SRA ID. If you need more help using Find a Solicitor, please look at our online help section. If you need further help call us on +44 (0)20 7320 5650 (Monday to Friday from 09:00 to 17:30 <span class="bold">charged at local call rates</span>) or <a href="mailto:findasolicitor@lawsociety.org.uk?subject=FAS%20Public%20enquiry">email us</a>.</p>
<p>The Law Society does not provide legal advice. Please <a href="http://www.lawsociety.org.uk/for-the-public/">read the Law Society guides to common legal issues</a> for information about getting advice from a solicitor.</p>


            </section>
            <section class="article-brief">
                <h2>Look for Law Society quality marks <i class="sprite icon-campaign"></i></h2>
<p>Organisations and individuals can be awarded a voluntary accreditation by the Law Society for different areas of law. When viewing quick search results, use the left-hand menu to only show accredited organisations that match your legal issue. Or you can use pro search to search for members of a specific accreditation scheme.</p>

            </section>      
        </div>
